The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The use of cache memories and the study of capacity-memory tradeoffs suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of coding techniques and rate-memory tradeoffs suggests a possible connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
